A  three-judge bench hearing a case filed by a council of elders challenging the construction of the Sh34 billion Itare dam will deliver judgment on July 27. Presiding Judge John Mutungi said they will give  a verdict after perusing the pleadings and submissions. During a visit to the site, the judges where guided by engineer Zablon Isaboke. Lawyers for the elders asked about adverse long-term effects. Judges Mutungi, Dalmas Ohungo and Mohammed Kuno visited the site on May 7. Read: Kipsigis elders challenge construction of Itare Dam in court Click here for the latest political news